---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PostCard from '../components/PostCard.astro';
import { getPublishedPostsSorted } from '../utils/post-filters';

const allPosts = await getCollection('posts');
const publishedPosts = getPublishedPostsSorted(allPosts);
---

<Layout
  title="Posts"
  description="Weekly reflections on working better and happier in tech. Essays on career growth, communication, and life lessons from beyond the code."
>
  <div class="posts-page">
    <h1 class="page-title">Posts</h1>

    <div class="posts-intro">
      <p>
        Sign up for my <a href="/newsletter">mailing list</a> to not miss anything! You can also find
        my blog posts on{' '}
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/newsletters/7394107177700970497/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a
        >, <a href="https://bouncingleaf.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Substack</a
        >,{' '}
        <a href="https://bouncingleaf.medium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Medium</a
        >,{' '}
        <a
          href="https://bsky.app/profile/leafjessicaroy.bsky.social"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Bluesky</a
        >, and maybe Facebook. <a href="#crosspost">How I do that...</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="posts-list">
      {publishedPosts.map((post) => <PostCard post={post} showCategories={true} />)}
    </div>

    <div class="posts-footer">
      <h2 id="crosspost">How does Leaf cross-post these blog posts?</h2>

      <p>Glad you asked, Leaf! (Yeah, these instructions are for my reference, haha)</p>

      <p>
        I start by <strong>posting</strong> here on my site. Zapier posts to Bluesky and Facebook Pages
        for me, so here are my steps:
      </p>

      <ol>
        <li>
          Go to the <a href="#latest">latest</a>. Open the post. Copy the URL.
        </li>
        <li>
          Click{' '}
          <a href="https://medium.com/p/import" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >https://medium.com/p/import</a
          >
          <ul>
            <li>Paste the post's URL. Click Import.</li>
            <li>Edit, fix photos, and Publish.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/newsletters/7394107177700970497/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn newsletter</a
          >: Copy text, paste, fix captions, link to my site.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://bouncingleaf.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Substack</a
          > &gt; Dashboard &gt; <strong>Settings</strong> (lower left).
          <ul>
            <li>
              Set the <strong># of posts on my feed</strong> (in my website settings) if needed
            </li>
            <li><strong>Import/Export</strong> &gt; <strong>Import Posts</strong></li>
            <li><strong>https://www.beyondwritingcode.com/feed</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Confirm</strong> the number of posts and ownership.</li>
            <li><strong>Clean up</strong> the post. Import links to the original.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Repost from my{' '}
          <a
            href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61584205431835"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Facebook Page</a
          > (via most recent repost)
        </li>
        <li>Check email for a draft for every-post subscribers. Check formatting and send.</li>
        <li>
          Thursday morning, check email again for a draft digest for weekly subscribers. Check
          formatting and send.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p>Whew! It's a bit tedious, but it works. Kind of ðŸ™‚</p>

      <p>
        Canonical URLs are handled: Substack and Medium set them up, LinkedIn relies on them being
        on your site and Yoast SEO sets them up on beyondwritingcode.com posts.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .posts-page {
    max-width: var(--content-max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
  }

  .posts-intro {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .posts-intro p {
    color: var(--color-gray);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .posts-intro a {
    color: var(--color-accent-teal);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .posts-intro a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-green);
  }

  .posts-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .posts-list :global(.post-image) {
    width: 25%;
  }

  .posts-footer {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  .posts-footer h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .posts-footer p,
  .posts-footer ol,
  .posts-footer ul {
    color: var(--color-gray);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .posts-footer ol {
    padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .posts-footer li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .posts-footer ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .posts-footer a {
    color: var(--color-accent-teal);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .posts-footer a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-green);
  }
</style>
